From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Scott <scott@elyanlabs.ai>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 15:39:14 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] 9036: Add e200 VLE PowerPC language support
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add e200 VLE PowerPC language support

Incorporate build fix from jobermayr — parameterize HREGSIZE/HREGBITS for 32/64-bit
Replace hardcoded 4-byte/32-bit values in SPE_FloatMulAdd.sinc with
HREGSIZE and HREGBITS defines, allowing the file to work correctly for
both 32-bit e200 (HREGSIZE=2, HREGBITS=16) and 64-bit ISA VLE
(HREGSIZE=4, HREGBITS=32). Also adds @if REGISTER_SIZE guards for
the bitmask constants in the scalar efs* instructions.

Credit: jobermayr (PR review comment)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

feat: add VLE ELF relocation handlers (types 216-232)

Implement all 17 VLE relocation types per the Power ISA VLE Extension,
matching the encoding logic in binutils bfd/elf32-ppc.c:

- R_PPC_VLE_REL8 (216): 8-bit PC-relative, 16-bit instruction
- R_PPC_VLE_REL15 (217): 15-bit PC-relative (BD15 form, e_bc)
- R_PPC_VLE_REL24 (218): 24-bit PC-relative (BD24 form, e_b/e_bl)
- R_PPC_VLE_LO16A/D (219-220): Low 16-bit split-immediate
- R_PPC_VLE_HI16A/D (221-222): High 16-bit split-immediate
- R_PPC_VLE_HA16A/D (223-224): High-adjusted 16-bit split-immediate
- R_PPC_VLE_SDA21/SDA21_LO (225-226): SDA-relative 16-bit
- R_PPC_VLE_SDAREL_LO16A/D (227-228): SDA-relative low 16-bit split
- R_PPC_VLE_SDAREL_HI16A/D (229-230): SDA-relative high 16-bit split
- R_PPC_VLE_SDAREL_HA16A/D (231-232): SDA-relative high-adj 16-bit split

The split-immediate encoding uses two helper methods (encodeSplit16A and
encodeSplit16D) derived directly from binutils ppc_elf_vle_split16():
  split16a: UI[0:4] at bits 20:16, UI[5:15] at bits 10:0
  split16d: UI[0:4] at bits 25:21, UI[5:15] at bits 10:0

Addresses unhandled relocation errors reported by MrsPeppu55 when loading
e200 VLE firmware binaries (R_PPC_VLE_REL24 and R_PPC_VLE_HA16A).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

fix: remove static from getSdaBaseForBlock to fix build
markAsError() is a non-static method inherited from
AbstractElfRelocationHandler, so getSdaBaseForBlock() cannot
be static. Fixes the Java compilation error:

  non-static method markAsError(...) cannot be referenced
  from a static context

Thanks to @jobermayr for identifying this in the build log.
